INFORMATION

Nolan, (born: January 27, 2005 [age 16]) better known online as Reverse Steve, is a Australian YouTuber and Photographer . He started his channel uploading solo using videos from his last channel (Maths & CO) . Some of his most viewed videos include him making tutorials that helps people find an answer to their question.

Reverse Steve is a French YouTuber living in Australia. He makes videos about various topics covering tech such as Minecraft tutorials, How to Fix, Android Phone tutorials and PC tutorials. He got his main boost when he found a good video topic about Toolbox Minecraft ( a Minecraft Bedrock client that gives you an advantage in survival mode). People love trolling and hacks for Minecraft so a channel that explains how to use this app will get attraction. Now he came back to Minecraft videos about tutorial videos such as Minecraft Resource Packs, Minecraft Shaders and “How to make” Minecraft 1.16.201 and 1.16.210 videos. This YouTuber is focusing on tech and tutorials.

Beginning

Reverse Steve first started his YouTube journey in 2019 under the name of Reverse Steve. He made some random videos about different topics, but none of them took off. One day, he decided to make a video about the Xbox App Profile Pic not working and in less than 1 day, he got 10,000 views, after this he knew that making tutorials about apps not working was the way to go. One day, he got recommended a video that Kipper, a YouTuber with about 2.4K subscribers, made about an app called Toolbox witch is a Minecraft mod/cheat that a lot of people were looking up on the search. Kipper had 20,000 in 3 days on his Toolbox Minecraft video, obviously Reverse Steve decided to make a video about toolbox not working, and got 10,000 views in a week, so he did more videos about Toolbox and garnered a great success with a recurring 5,000 or more to 20 videos one after the other. He did all the tutorials possible about the Toolbox app which gained the channel 2,000 subscribers and 500,000 views in less then 6 months. Then he decided to change his name from Reverse Steve to Toolbox Minecraft so he could rank #1 on search and get more subscribers because his subscribe button will be the first thing that showed up on Toolbox Minecraft (Called Channel Jumping). This was a very successful idea that gained the Toolbox Minecraft 3,000 subscribers in less then 2 months.

Everything was going great until he did all the tutorials possible on his to-do list (this is still a problem today). He did make some videos about Among US mods/cheats and gotten 21K then 51K on these videos. There was one problem with this new discovery, it was that he had to delete the videos if he did not want to lose his YouTube Channel, it is better to loose 100000K views than 820000+K views. This discouraged Toolbox Minecraft from making a new video for 1 month, he did make a among us video that got 12K and stopped here. On the December the 2nd there was a new Minecraft update and on the 13 of December he will restart making videos. He decided to change his name to Rainbow Steve to try ranking #1 on search to go back to where he started, then he changed it back to Reverse Steve one month after when seing that the name did not change the number of views or subscribers you get. (Reverse Steve —> Toolbox Minecraft —> Rainbow Steve—> Reverse Steve).

This is just a start to Reverse Steve, he has learned how YouTube worked with this one year of full on training and he is here to show what you can do if you don’t want to show your face or voice to the world.
